title: Things I’m Loving Friday #262
body:
Friday is here! This week felt a little all over the place with New Year’s Eve, New Year’s Day and no preschool in the mix but it’s Friday nonetheless and the weekend has arrived. Woop!

(Pic from our early NYE celebration this year with some of our closest friends and our little ones!) 

Our weekend plans are pretty minimal which is 100 percent intentional. We need to get our house in order since it currently looks like Christmas threw up all over our dining room table and our Christmas tree is still up and shedding approximately 1,000 pine needles per second.

Maybe putting all of our Christmas stuff up in the attic will be our rockin’ Friday night activity!? Please don’t try to hide your jealousy.

I am glad I was able to get back to blogging a bit this week — it’s kind of crazy how much I miss it when I miss even a few days — and I’m happy to be sharing my weekly Things I’m Loving Friday post with you guys again after a mini hiatus. Today’s post includes a few things that are making me smile lately and, as always, I’d love to hear a little bit about something you’re loving this week as well!

Have a great first weekend of 2019, my friends!

Things I’m Loving Friday 

  • O-Venture Key Ring

My mom has one of these key rings and has raved about it for years. I’ve always admired it from afar but this year I not-so-subtly hinted that I might like one of my own for Christmas. My sister surprised me with the rose gold version and I absolutely love it! I am surprised just how handy I’m already finding it, especially since slipping the ring around my wrist frees up both of my hands which I need pretty much at all times when I’m out and about with two kids in tow.

I’ve been sliding the key ring around my wrist along with my favorite wristlet pouch I use to carry the essentials (a couple of diapers, wipes, lip balm, healing ointment, a spare onesie) and it’s perfect! I have two free hands to use to carry Ryder, hold Chase’s hand, etc. Until I miraculously grow a third arm, I appreciate anything that allows me to have a free hand!

  • Ryder’s First Tooth

Guess whose first tooth emerged on New Year’s Eve!? Based on just how much Ryder’s been gnawing on everything and drooling, his first tooth has been dying to break through for weeks! Ryder’s left lower middle tooth finally made its debut on Monday and I now feel like my baby is growing up waaay too fast.

  • Jazzercise with My Mom and Sister

This didn’t make my Christmas 2018 post only because I was trying my best to keep things concise, but on Christmas Eve, I attended a Jazzercise class with my mom and sister and was reminded, yet again, how much I LOVE that class! It’s so energizing, uplifting and encouraging and the environment of nearly every Jazzercise studio I’ve attended has always been so positive and welcoming.

My mom and sister regularly attend Jazzercise in Jacksonville and I loved joining them for a holiday-themed workout. We had a blast dancing and stretching to holiday music on Christmas Eve morning and attending the class made me miss the days when I’d regularly join my mom and Leslie for Jazzercise classes during random breaks in the school year when I’d be home from college. We even attended one of Jazzercise’s giant on-location events together back in 2012!

  • Chase’s Fireman Jacket + Boots

Right before Christmas, Chase’s latest Stitch Fix Kids delivery arrived and it included his favorite clothing items to date: A fireman rain coat and fireman rain boots. He plays imagination games all day every day, so this rainy day apparel is currently doubling as dress up items for “Fire Chase,” as he likes to call himself. And yes, that would be his “fireman pose” above. I don’t know where he comes up with this stuff!

  • Friday Flashbacks

This Week’s Meal Plan: 5 Meatless Meals (I had a few of you request more plant-based recipes on the blog in 2019 which I definitely hope to share but in the interim, here are five meatless meals we loved in 2018!)

10 Most Used Kitchen Items (A few of my kitchen must-haves to make cooking, baking and cleanup a little easier!)

Question of the Day

What is one thing making you smile this week?

summary: Why Do Your Muscles Need Protein?
title: Why Do Your Muscles Need Protein?
body:
The muscles are the organs that are between the bones and skin, are responsible for producing body movement. They are the most flexible organs of the human body, they can contract and relax without breaking. This also allows us to develop and strengthen them by exercising. Protein helps to improve muscles.

Proteins are the ones in charge of giving energy to our muscles and the ones that maintain the muscular mass in an optimal way. Proteins are essential nutrients, we need them to live. They are macromolecules and are made up of smaller molecules called amino acids.

The functions of proteins are several, the main one is to build tissue, especially muscle, hence the importance of their consumption to have strong and healthy muscles. In addition to repairing tissue or organs when we have a wound.

They also help to regulate and synthesize other essential elements such as hormones.

Some proteins cannot be produced by the human body so we need to get them through food. By eating these foods, our body breaks down and disintegrates amino acids to make its own proteins.

Read on to find out everything you need to know about proteins to help you have strong, healthy muscles.

How Much Protein Do We Need?

The amount of protein we need varies according to various criteria such as age, sex and the physical condition of each person. In addition, pregnant or breastfeeding women have a special need. Here’s how to find out how much you generally need:

blog.title: Diary of a Fat Girl
blog.description:
Hello, my name is Kaitlin and I am currently a 22 yr old college student graduating in May 2019 with a BS degree in mechanical engineering. This blog primarily documents my journey as I attempt to lose over 100 lbs and develop a healthier lifestyle. I am not perfect; in fact, this blog is dedicated mostly to my physical, mental, and emotional struggles. I try to be as real as possible with all my struggles, specifically with being a healthier version of myself. Because of life, I am not the most active blog; however, I am trying to at least reblog or post something once a day and update about my life as often as possible. I hope you join this journey with me because its gonna be a long one!

Below are my current stats as of March 19, 2019:

Age: 22

Height: 5'7"

Starting Weight: 295.8lb

Current Weight: 295.8lb

Total Loss: +/-0.0lb

title: Yesterday and today's plan (2)
body:
Yesterday did not go as planned at all. I ate well for breakfast and lunch, and even went to the gym. But I only walked for 40 min because I was stuck on hold for 20 min for a 1 min phone call. Then I rushed home to eat dinner because I had plans that evening, to find out dinner wasn’t made. Ends up mom got pizza at 7, so I’m starving, eat a ton of pizza and wings, went out with my sister, and then got ice cream because I said “fuck it.” That was not my best day and so far I’m not doing too good for my “ new year, new me.”

Today I’m trying to do better. I had the same breakfast of eggs, toast w butter and black coffee. I didnt pack a whole lot for lunch, but its calorie heavy. I got more black bean salsa and chips along with cheese and pineapple mustard. I’m really hoping that keeps me full. This morning I was so tired and therefore couldn’t come up with anything to eat so I packed what I could find. This weekend I plan on meal prepping all my meals and snacks for the whole week. So we shall see how that goes… I have no idea what’s for dinner but hopefully it’s somewhat healthy.

summary: Hi. I'm going back to uni after winter break and I'm really anxious about it. I have constant negative thoughts that I'm the...
question: Hi. I'm going back to uni after winter break and I'm really anxious about it. I have constant negative thoughts that I'm the worst there (even if I know that there are people with even worse grades) and that I'll not pass any class and they'll kick me out. Just thinking about it triggering my panic attacks. I'm especially worried about my math classes because I feel like prof. really hates me there and he threaten me that I might not pass his classes. Please help me, I'm so anxious about it all!
answer:
Hi love, 

I’m sorry your professor said that. Is it because you didn’t do well on an assignment or test? Did he give a reason why he thinks you’ll fail?

First of all, I just want you to take a deep breath. Your worth is not measured by your GPA or your degree. Your mental health is more important than any of that. There is so much more to life than school, and you need to remember that. 

Second of all, I highly doubt that you failed all of your classes. Even if you do fail your math class, as terrifying as that is, it won’t be the end of the world. You can retake the course, get a tutor, or spend some extra time on the topics that are a struggle. And I doubt that your prof is the only one that teaches those courses at your uni. Try to see if you can sit in the class of another prof. 

I did so bad in my first semester of uni. I had a 1.9 GPA and the expulsion line was at 1.8 GPA so I got away with an academic probation. I’m telling you this, that sometimes, even if failure is inevitable, it opens up a door to other possibilities that you would not have considered otherwise. I’m now taking other courses and I have a better understanding of what I want and why I failed and how to do better next time. 

You are strong and you will get through this. I believe in you. Good luck!

💋
